President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for various positions. Steven J. Menashi of New York is nominated to serve as Circuit Judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit. Jodi W. Dishman of Oklahoma is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Western District of Oklahoma. Karen S. Marston of Pennsylvania is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Pennsylvania. Richard E. Myers II of North Carolina is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of North Carolina. Sarah E. Pitlyk of Missouri is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Missouri. Anuraag "Raag" Singhal of Florida is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of Florida. David M. DeVillers of Ohio is nominated to serve as the United States Attorney for the Southern District of Ohio. Thomas L. Leonard III of Michigan is nominated to serve as the United States Attorney for the Western District of Michigan. Owen M. Cypher of Michigan is nominated to serve as the United States Marshal for the Eastern District of Michigan. Ralph Sozio of New York is nominated to serve as the United States Marshal for the Southern District of New York.